== Custom shortcuts
   [#custom]

To create your own application keyboard shortcut in the
$app(Keyboard) settings:

[steps]
* Click the $gui[.button](+) button. The $gui(Custom Shortcut)
  window will appear.

* Type a $gui(Name) to identify the shortcut, and a $gui(Command)
  to run an application, then click $gui(Add). For example, if you
  wanted the shortcut to open $app(Rhythmbox), you could name it
  $input(Music) and use the $input(rhythmbox) command.

* Click $gui(Disabled) in the row that was just added. When it
  changes to $gui(New accelerator…), hold down the desired shortcut
  key combination.

The command name that you type should be a valid system command. You can
check that the command works by opening a Terminal and typing it in there.
The command that opens an application cannot have the same name as the
application itself.

If you want to change the command that is associated with a custom
keyboard shortcut, double-click the $em(name) of the shortcut. The
$gui(Custom Shortcut) window will appear, and you can edit the
command.
